cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.ET, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a formalisation of stream processing components using Isabelle/HOL+Isar, which is a logical framework. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of the formalisation in the development of interactive systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as Isabelle/HOL+Isar is a programming language and the paper presents a formalisation of stream processing components. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of the formalisation in different application areas, which could be considered emerging technologies. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper presents case studies in process control and automotive systems, which are related to systems and control.
